extends ../layout

block content
  h2= message

  p.
    This is a sample page demonstrating Pug4j template engine integration
    with Spring Boot and Domain-Driven Design architecture.

  h3 Project Features
  ul
    each feature in features
      li= feature

  h3 Architecture Patterns
  ul
    li Domain-Driven Design (DDD)
      ul
        li Aggregates, Entities, Value Objects
        li Domain Events & Services
        li Factories & Specifications
    li Clean Architecture
      ul
        li Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters)
        li Onion Architecture (Dependency Inversion)
        li Framework-Independent Domain
    li Testing
      ul
        li ArchUnit for Architecture Enforcement
        li Comprehensive Test Coverage

  h3 Template Engine
  p.
    This page is rendered using <strong>Pug4j</strong>, a Java implementation
    of the Pug template engine (formerly Jade).

  h4 Pug Features Demonstrated:
  ul
    li Variables: <code>title = "#{title}"</code>
    li Iteration: Looping through features
    li Template inheritance: This page extends layout.pug
    li Attributes: Dynamic HTML attributes
    li Mixins: Reusable template blocks

  style.
    h2 { color: #2c3e50; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    h3 { color: #34495e; margin-top: 30px; border-bottom: 2px solid #3498db; padding-bottom: 10px; }
    h4 { color: #7f8c8d; margin-top: 20px; }
    ul { margin-left: 20px; }
    li { margin-bottom: 8px; }
    code { background: #f4f4f4; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-family: monospace; }
    p { line-height: 1.8; }
